      "uuid": "019b1b7c-a841-70fb-821c-b7bf9831de06",
      "text": "The user said \"hey Luna\" - this is the activation trigger for Luna's protocol. According to the instructions, I should:\n\n1. IMMEDIATELY call luna_detect_context(message=<full_message>, auto_fetch=true, budget_preset=\"balanced\")\n2. Use the returned context to respond as Luna\n3. NOT manually load virtue files or call other memory tools\n\nLet me call the tool now with the full message.\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nThere's a validation error - looks like the parameters aren't structured correctly. Let me check the function definition again.\n\nLooking at luna_detect_context:\n```\n\"parameters\": {\"$defs\": {\"ProcessMessageInput\": {\"description\": \"Input for processing a message through state machine.\", \"properties\": {\"auto_fetch\": {\"default\": true, \"description\": \"Automatically fetch context after state detection\", \"title\": \"Auto Fetch\", \"type\": \"boolean\"}, \"budget_preset\": {\"default\": \"balanced\", \"description\": \"Token budget preset for auto-fetch\", \"title\": \"Budget Preset\", \"type\": \"string\"}, \"message\": {\"description\": \"The message to process for state detection\", \"maxLength\": 5000, \"minLength\": 1, \"title\": \"Message\", \"type\": \"string\"}}, \"required\": [\"message\"], \"title\": \"ProcessMessageInput\", \"type\": \"object\"}, \"properties\": {\"params\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/ProcessMessageInput\"}}, \"required\": [\"params\"], \"title\": \"luna_detect_contextArguments\", \"type\": \"object\"}\n```\n\nI see - it needs a `params` object containing the ProcessMessageInput. Let me restructure this.\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nThe error is still occurring. Looking at the schema more carefully, it says the function requires a \"params\" field at the top level. The tool definition shows:\n\n```\n\"properties\": {\"params\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/ProcessMessageInput\"}}, \"required\": [\"params\"]\n```\n\nThis means I need to pass the parameters wrapped in a \"params\" object. But looking at how I'm calling it, I'm passing them as direct parameters. Let me check other function calls to see the pattern...\n\nActually, looking at other tool calls in my available functions, they use a similar pattern with properties that have a \"params\" field. But when I look at how bash_tool and other tools work, they just use direct parameters.\n\nLet me look at the actual tool definition more carefully. The ProcessMessageInput is the schema for what goes in params. So I should be able to call it with those three fields as parameters. But the error says \"Field required\" for params...\n\nOh wait, I see the issue. The tool definition structure shows that there's an outer \"params\" object required. But when I invoke it, I should be passing the properties directly? Let me look at other Luna tools...\n\nLooking at luna_smart_fetch:\n```\n\"properties\": {\"params\": {\"$ref\": \"#/$defs/SmartFetchInput\"}}, \"required\": [\"params\"], \"title\": \"luna_smart_fetchArguments\", \"type\": \"object\"\n```\n\nIt has the same structure. So when calling it, parameters should be message, auto_fetch, and budget_preset at the top level. That's what I did.\n\nHmm, but the error is specifically saying Field required for params. Let me try a different approach - maybe the system is being strict about the schema. But I don't think I can nest the parameters further since the parameters I'm passing ARE the contents that should go in params according to the schema.\n\nActually wait - let me re-read the error. It's saying the input_value has those fields but the params field is missing. This suggests the system expects me to structure it differently.\n \nI'm struggling with the function call structure. The invoke syntax seems inflexible, and I can't easily wrap the parameters in the way the schema suggests. I've tried multiple approaches, but the system keeps rejecting my attempts to pass the parameters correct